and the solutions are 
$$r(t)=(1+ce^{-2t})^{\frac{-1}{2}}, \,\,\,\,\,\,\theta(t)=-(t-\alpha).$$ So my question is how did they solve $r'$.  It's been a while since I've take differential equations and I need help how to solve it.
